                                                   Cup hockey schedule advanced
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The International Hockey Federation (FIH) has decided to advance the dates of the World Cup by a week to avoid a clash with the Indian Premier League (IPL).         
	In a press release on Friday, the FIH said the World Cup in Delhi will now be held from February 28 to March 13, 2010.         
	Earlier, the championship was scheduled from March 7 to 20.         
	The IPL is scheduled from March 12 to April 25.         
	Hockey India president Ashok Matto said: Yes, the dates have been changed to avoid clash with IPL.         
	A total of 12 teams, including hosts India, will participate in the World Cup to be played in the National Stadium in Delhi.                                                                                                                       
